Class SortStringType

java.lang.Object

          ezvcard.types.SortStringType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<VCardType>
public class SortStringType
extends TextType

Defines a string that should be used when an application sorts this vCard in some way.

The SORT-STRING type is not supported in 4.0. Instead, use the StructuredNameType.setSortAs(java.lang.String) and/or OrganizationType.setSortAs(java.lang.String...) methods.

Code sample (2.1, 3.0) 

 VCard vcard = new VCard();
 StructuredNameType n = new StructuredNameType();
 n.setFamily("d'Armour");
 n.setGiven("Miles");
 vcard.setStructuredName(n);
 SortStringType sortString = new SortStringType("Armour");
 vcard.setSortString(sortString);

Code sample (4.0) 

 VCard vcard = new VCard();
 StructuredNameType n = new StructuredNameType();
 n.setFamily("d'Armour");
 n.setGiven("Miles");
 n.setSortAs("Armour");
 vcard.setStructuredName(n);

Property name: SORT-STRING

Supported versions: 2.1, 3.0

Author:
Michael Angstadt
